The train comes to a stop. Outside, you can see a small station. People begin to get off the train, and the personell going through the corridors give you no choice. You get off at the station with the others. You think you can hear the word "police" somewhere, and you think you can see the big man who took the tape recorder disappears around the corner of the station building.

You are standing on the platform where the train that took you here stopped. The train is still here, standing still on the tracks. The whole area is walled in exept to the north, where the small station building is. On it is a sign saying "A-Station Mittstädts". East of the station building, to your northeast, there is also an opening. On the other side, you can see a street.
You can go south, north or northeast.
