You are inside the station building. The building is not very big, and the room you are in ends a short bit to your east, where there is a closed door, and west, where there is a wall. The walls are almost white and the floor is a faint grey. Some passengers are in here. You recognize a few of them, but none are of any interest.
You can go south or north.
You can see a trash can.
You can hear some of the passengers talking:
"...police. They found someting on the train. They are checking everyone and blocking the  street."
"Typical. We'll never get to the hotel. Remember to thank your mother for the trip."
They leave the station to the north.
