You are standing on the west-east street running north of the station building. There are not many people walking here. The street ends a bit further to the west. To the east, there are many people standing in line before a police roadblood.
There are, of course, several buildings to your north. Most buildings are made of bricks. There seems to be no usable entrance here.
You can go southeast, east, south or west.
