The street ends here, with no way to go on. To your south is the wall outside the train station, and to the west is the back of a building. You can still see the police roadblock off to the east. There is a cheap-looking hotel here, with the entrance to your north..
You can go east.
> x hotel

> x hotel
It looks quite run-down, and is made of brick like many of the other buildings. Its sign says "Hotel Zuchstadt" and the building has at least three or four floors.
> enter hotel

> enter hotel

You are in the lobby of a small, run-down hotel. The lobby is no larger than a regular living room, and the wooden desk stands near one of the inner corners. Behind it stand the hotel manager. At the western wall, under the letters "BAR", an entrance to a restaurant is located. The door is closed, though, with a sign saying "Schliesst/Closed".  With its walls a faint blue and the floor made of imitation of wood, it really does resemble a living room. There is a sofa (propably uncomfortable) with a small table and a magazine holder close to it. In the other inner corner of the room (the northeastern) stairs lead up. On a sign pointing upwards, you can see the numbers "201-205".
You can go up, south or out.
You can see a hotel manager.
> talk to manager

> talk to manager
You walk up to the manager.
"Gruz... Hello, and welcome to Hotel Zuchstadt!"
Your appearance must have given you away again.
"Would you like a room or something else?"
What do you say?
1: I'd like that room.
2: Where am I?
3: I'm looking for someone.
4: Where can I get a drink?
5: Sorry, just looking around.
> 1
"A room for one, then..."
He writes something in a notebook from his pocket.
"Would you like breakfast in the morning? Oh, sorry, we cannot offer that at the moment!"
He looks somewhat embarassed.
"The price is 15 Thaler a night, and you pay when you leave. Your room is number 204, up the stairs."
He hands you a small key.
"Welcome, and have a nice evening!"
> up

> up

You are in a corridor at the hotel's second floor. The corridor runs from east to west, with the stairs down furthest to the east and more rooms to the west. The floor is neatly carpeted, and the walls are plain. In your immediate vicinity are rooms 201 and 202.
You can go down or west.
