You fall down on the floor, in a pool of your own blood. It reaches above your face and pours into your mouth. Your lungs feel full of your own blood, and your eyes are ringing. The blood enters your body every way possible. Somewhere, you hear  a sound... like someone is knocking on a door.
You are in the hotel room you rented. It is not very big, and not any cleaner. The window is located on the north side of the room, while the exit is to the south. There is not a lot in here, but there is an uncomfortable bed, a small chair and some non-descript hotel room furniture.
