You are standing on a ledge on the wall of the hotel building, tightly squeezed against the wall. Below you is the street, and to the east this ledge ends with a small drainpipe. You can see another ledge outside the next hotel room, but you cannot reach it from here.
You can go west or east.
You can see a drainpipe.
> climb drainpipe

> climb drainpipe
You grab onto the black drainpipe.

You are holding onto the thing, black drainpipe east of the ledge outside your hotel room. You could easily get back onto the ledge. To your east is another ledge, outside the next hotel room, but you could not reach it. If you climbed down the drainpipe, you would end up in the alley below without being able to climb back up since the drainpipe is broken and ends almost two metres above ground.
You can go west or down.
> down

