> e

You are in a small bookstore, which can be entered by the entrance door, which opens inwards. There is no one behind the counter, which is located by the southern wall. To the east, a small door, slightly ajar, seems to reveal a staff room. The room is dimly lit by a discrete lamp in the ceiling, and there are two shelves here; one (a large one) by the northern wall and one (smaller) roughly in the middle of the room, turned to face the entrance door.
You can go west.
The man in the coat has almost caught up with you.
> tip over small shelf

> tip over small shelf
