You are standing est of a parking lot, easily accesible through climbing over the low railing to your west. To your east you can see the facade of a concrete building; there is a bookstore at ground level, with big windows. The road you are standing on continues to the north and south of here.
You can go south, east or north.
> n

> n
You continue walking northwards without knowing where the direction will take you. You walk quickly to get away from the trouble behind you, still with the unanswered questions lingering at the back of your mind. You start walking even faster.

As you turn around a corner, somebody grabs you by the shoulder. You can feel the needle enter the back of your neck, and before a moment has passed everything seems dark and far away.

You come to, feeling quite tired of getting hit, doped, tied up and generally mistreated by the world. As you look around, still dizzy, you find yourself in a small and dark room, with the curtains drawn. It seems to be an office. You can see a dark brown oak desk in front of two bookcases, filled with books you cannot make out. There is a rug under the chair you are sitting on. Around you and the chair, the rope is tightly tied, preventing you from moving or using your hands in any way.

After an eternity of about three minutes, somebody enters the room. Somebody with a familiar, bald head and an unamused expression in his face. As far as he is concerned, he is likely in charge.

"You fucked up good, didn't you?"

If possible, his expression grows even more sour.

"We knew about you from the beginning, you know."

He leans back somewhat, with his hands resting on the desk behind him.

"We knew you were not to be trusted. We only kept you among us to knew WHOM not to trust."

Finally, you get to see his smile even if not very geuine.

"It was you and that idiot, Frank."

He stands up in the middle of the room again.

"Oh, we know you didn't know about each  other... But that's what happens when there are several sides to pick. Do you even know what I'm talking about? You seem... stupid today."

In fact, you do not, which you readily inform him of.

"Frank is that fucker in you compartment. The miserable idiot that YOU killed. Yes, you did in fact kill him even if you might have... some trouble remembering it."

There is that beautiful smile again.

"You see, this mison is not business as usual. You know of the situation. You know of the tension. You might not know what information you recorded on the train, but it's worth something, all right. At least it is worth a lot to me."

"You are propably still a bit tired, but I will be back soon."

He walks past you and hits you in the face. The punch is not too hard, but it makes your head spin all over again. The man leaves the room.

You are in a quite small, dark room. This little office, with the curtains drawn, contains a desk in front of a bookcase. On the desk is a large, heavy paperweight. On the floor is a thick rug, with your chair on it. You are tied to the chair and cannot move.
You are alone now, but still tied to the chair. Your head is pounding and you feel miserable. If there is a way out, it woul be a good idea to find it now.
